This article is an official order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. It states that certain parts of the Manual for Courts-Martial, United States, are being amended. These amendments will take effect immediately. The order clarifies that the amendments will not retroactively punish any acts or omissions that were not punishable at the time they occurred. It also states that ongoing nonjudicial punishment proceedings, restraints, investigations, referral of charges, and trials will not be invalidated and can continue as if the amendments had not been made. The order is dated January 26, 2022, and is signed by President Biden.